            {
              "id": "4cc3509",
              "elType": "widget",
              "settings": {
                "editor": "<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Costa Rica, a country once dominated by conventional agriculture with sprawling pasture and cacao fields, witnessed a remarkable transformation in the 1990’s. Like its neighboring nations, the encroachment of agriculture had been gradually displacing primary jungles and disrupting animal habitats. However, a green awakening was on the horizon, and regenerative projects began to take root, promising a more sustainable and harmonious future.</span></p><p><!-- notionvc: 17339c47-4e6e-4cec-95f3-7d470520a423 --></p>",
